   477	## Fork protocol — 9 seam touch-points
   478	
   479	The boundary passes only integers, booleans, immutable integer collections,
   480	and callbacks; no Fiber, lane bitmask, or update-queue object crosses it.
   481	
   482	1. **F1 — write classification and token claim.** At a signal write, report
   483	   whether it is deferred and its lazily minted stable batch token. Tokens are
   484	   never reused while live or unswept.
   485	2. **F2 — pass lifecycle and callstack truth.** Report
   486	   start(rootId, included tokens, pin, lineage), yield, resume, completion,
   487	   commit, and discard. A handler in a yield gap has no render frame. F2 also
   488	   supplies the inherited discard-all-WIP control used at the R8 horizon.
   489	3. **F3 — per-root commit lock-in.** Report the generation-checked rootId,
   490	   committed token set, and each committing watermark. Ordering is F9
   491	   publication, folds/lock-view remint, durable watcher/effect drains, then
   492	   layout. S5-R12 removes only the library's commitBaseline capture.
   493	4. **F4 — retirement.** Exactly once per token, report committed flag and a
   494	   retirement point on the global sequence line. `committed=false` still
   495	   folds writes. Async actions park this edge until settlement.
   496	5. **F5 — lane-scoped execution.** `runInBatch(token, callback)` inserts the
   497	   callback's React update into that live token's lanes; a retired token returns
   498	   `RETIRED`, allowing urgent fallback.
   499	6. **F6 — render lineage.** Mint an identity per root and batch selection,
   500	   stable across its retries/replays and dead at commit/abandon.
   501	7. **F7 — DOM mutation window.** Edge-triggered begin/end facts delimit the
   502	   mutation interval for integration policy; no sampled reconciler state.
   503	8. **F8 — async-action parking and continuation carrier.** Preserve token
   504	   identity across transformed/platform-supported continuations and registered
   505	   host callbacks; a continuation that outlives retirement degrades to ambient
   506	   classification with a dev warning.
   507	9. **F9 — hook-becomes-current publication.** Emit the generation-checked
   508	   staged evaluator identity only for the hook version that becomes current,
   509	   including hidden Offscreen commits; emit nothing for discarded/error-
   510	   abandoned alternates; order publication before same-commit folds.
   511	
   512	Version skew is loud: bindings feature-detect the exact protocol version and
   513	reject stock or incompatible React. With no listener, each reconciler site is
   514	one null check. Rebase drill: if React renames lanes, moves phases, or rewrites
   515	queues, only the fork adapters that re-establish F1–F9 and their tests move;
   516	the signals library changes zero lines.
   517	
