   526	| 2 | A transition write is deferred and receives the transition's token. | F1 |
   527	| 3 | One batch's token is stable across nested calls and action continuations. | F1/F8 |
   528	| 4 | A live or retired-unswept token is never reused; forced-small serials fail loudly rather than collide. | F1/F4 |
   529	| 5 | passStart reports exact rootId, included-token set, pin, and lineage before user render code. | F2/F6 |
   530	| 6 | yield removes render context from the JS callstack; resume restores the same immutable pass frame. | F2 |
   531	| 7 | A handler in a yield gap reads/writes ambient newest state and gets its own batch. | F1/F2 |
   532	| 8 | Each pass has exactly one terminal completion/commit/discard path; a restart is a new pass. | F2 |
   533	| 9 | Retirement fires exactly once for committed and committed-false tokens. | F4 |
